    "title": "Reflecting on the Project",
    "long_instructions": "#### As students work on their cybersecurity projects, balancing technical structure with creative exploration is key — thoughtful scaffolds, guided analysis of security trade-offs, and opportunities for peer critique will help them transform their ideas into well-reasoned, user-focused solutions.\r\n\r\n## Discussion Questions: \r\n#### 1️⃣ How will I help students move beyond surface-level issues to identify deeper security problems in a system?\r\n\r\n#### 2️⃣ What strategies can I use to support students in balancing creativity (e.g., personified defense mechanisms) with technical accuracy?\r\n\r\n#### 3️⃣ How will I guide students to explain trade-offs in their solutions rather than focusing only on the “best” fix?\r\n\r\n#### *These questions are just starting points for reflection and discussion — there is no need to answer all of them. Focus on the ones that resonate most with your teaching experience and goals.*\r\n\r\n\r\n<div style=\"display: flex; align-items: left; margin:20px 0px 30px 0px\">\r\n\r\n<a href=\"https://forum.code.org\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">\r\n<img src=\"https://images.code.org/7dbe63a051fbad4ef262d6ab710e2966-image-1731959037460.png\" style=\"width: auto; height: 100px;\"  alt=\"A browser with two text boxes, both including an avatar and lines of text.\"></a>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"background-color: #007786; border-radius: 20px 20px 20px 20px; color: #000000; width: 80%; margin-left: 5%; margin-right: 5%; padding: 10px 10px 5px 10px;\">\r\n\r\n<p style=\"color: white; line-height: 1.5; margin-left: 10px; margin-right: 10px; font-size: 18px\"><b>Post to the Code.org Forum - Not Available During Pilot</b></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"color: white; line-height: 1.2; margin-left: 10px; margin-right: 10px; font-size: 18px\">Share your response and read other educators' ideas on the forum! Click on the icon to the left to direct to our forum post.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n",
